(
<figureCitation id="13422A46FFB1BD61FEF615C3DCE2B8AB" box="[376,438,1715,1741]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1314,1331]" captionTargetBox="[215,1456,183,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-386@8.[748,1285,716,1286]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 3. — Dentaries of Palaeogale dorothiae MacDonald, 1963: A, lingual view (JODA 6177);B, occlusal view (JODA 6177);C, buccal view (JODA 6177); D, lingual view (JODA 5893); E, occlusal view (JODA 5893); F, buccal view (JODA 5893). Scale bars: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448638" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6448638/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="C6FB0378FFB1BD61FE4D15C3DF47B8AB" box="[451,531,1715,1741]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="7.[133,143,220,237]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. — Measurements of the lower dentition. Abbreviations: APL, anterior-posterior length; TW, transverse width; –, not available; *, type specimen. All measurements are in mm. †, measured scaled figure or image in ImageJ." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF06664BFFB1BD61FF0B13ACDFB1BF65" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" tableUuid="DF06664BFFB1BD61FF0B13ACDFB1BF65">Table 2</tableCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3636548FFB1BD61FF0A159EDFE6B9E3" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FF0A159EDFA5B946" blockId="7.[131,774,1773,1824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
REFERRED SPECIMENS. — 
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FEF6159EDCECB960" box="[376,440,1774,1798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">JODA</collectionCode>
6177 left fragmentary dentary with p4-m1. 
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FF5F1478DC45B946" box="[209,273,1800,1824]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">JODA</collectionCode>
5893 right fragmentary dentary with p2 and p4.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FF0A1449DFE6B9E3" blockId="7.[131,776,1849,1926]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
OCCURRENCE. — JDNM-140, Lonerock, Gilliam County, 
<collectingRegion id="49BDF821FFB1BD61FD391449DE50B937" box="[695,772,1849,1873]" country="United States of America" name="Oregon" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Oregon</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F36E7653FFB1BD61FF0D1423DDE2B90D" box="[131,182,1875,1899]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">USA</collectingCountry>
. Kimberly Member, John Day Formation. Precise locality information available to qualified researchers upon request.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3636548FFB1BD61FF0A14EFDF05B98D" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" type="multiple">
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FF0A14EFDF05B98D" blockId="7.[132,776,1950,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
AGE. — Late Oligocene in the Late Arikareean (Ar3) 
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FD2914EFDE57B9D1" box="[679,771,1951,1975]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">NALMA</collectionCode>
, between the Tin Roof Tuff (25.3 Ma) and the UNSM JD-BC-3 tuff (23.5-23.8 Ma) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FEDA14A3DF17B98D" author="FREMD T. J. &amp; WHISTLER D. P." box="[340,579,2003,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="159 - 169" refId="ref6738" refString="FREMD T. J. &amp; WHISTLER D. P. 2009. - Preliminary description of a new microvertebrate assemblage from the Arikareean (Early Miocene) John Day Formation, Central Oregon. Museum of Northern Arizona Bulletin 65: 159 - 169." type="journal article" year="2009">Fremd &amp; Whistler 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3636548FFB1BD61FCA310E4D8FBBDA1" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FCA310E4D8FBBDA1" blockId="7.[811,1456,916,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FCA310E4DE8CBDCD" box="[813,984,916,940]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">SPECIES DIAGNOSIS</collectionCode>
. — The p4 is without a posterior accessory cusp and the protoconid of the m1 is not expanded laterally (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FB7210DFD8F5BDA1" author="MACDONALD J. R." box="[1276,1441,943,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="139 - 240" refId="ref7214" refString="MACDONALD J. R. 1963. - The Miocene Faunas from the Wounded Knee Area of Western South Dakota. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 125 (3): 139 - 240. http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1259" type="journal article" year="1963">MacDonald 1963</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3636548FFB1BD61FCA31085D9CCBA88" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FCA31085DEE9BA6B" blockId="7.[811,1464,1013,1262]" box="[813,957,1013,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FCA31085DEE9BA6B" box="[813,957,1013,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">DESCRIPTION</collectionCode>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FCA31764D9CCBA88" blockId="7.[811,1464,1013,1262]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FCA31764DE20BA48" box="[813,884,1044,1070]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">JODA</collectionCode>
5893 has no posterior accessory cusp on p4; however, there is a small enamel anomaly on the posterior edge. There is an alveolus for p3. The p2 crown is stretched forward with an upturned posterior heel. 
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FBEC1704D9FEBAE8" box="[1122,1194,1140,1166]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">JODA</collectionCode>
6177 is broken behind the c, and there is no p2 alveoli. There is no p4 accessory cusp. The m1 protoconid is not expanded laterally. See 
<tableCitation id="C6FB0378FFB1BD61FAB417C4D8DDBAA8" box="[1338,1417,1204,1230]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="7.[133,143,220,237]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. — Measurements of the lower dentition. Abbreviations: APL, anterior-posterior length; TW, transverse width; –, not available; *, type specimen. All measurements are in mm. †, measured scaled figure or image in ImageJ." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF06664BFFB1BD61FF0B13ACDFB1BF65" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" tableUuid="DF06664BFFB1BD61FF0B13ACDFB1BF65">Table 2</tableCitation>
for measurements of both specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3636548FFB1BD61FCA31664D8FBB96A" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FCA31664DEE9BB4A" blockId="7.[810,1457,1300,1805]" box="[813,957,1300,1326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">COMPARISON</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC636C3FFB1BD61FCA31643D8FBB96A" blockId="7.[810,1457,1300,1805]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">
Both specimens match the species diagnosis in the absence of the p4 accessory cusp. They are both too large to be 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D40FFB1BD61FAAA1624D8DEBB0B" baseAuthorityName="Hayes" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[1316,1418,1364,1390]" class="Mammalia" family="Odobenidae" genus="Palaeogale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FAAA1624D867BB0B" box="[1316,1331,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FACE1624D8DEBB0B" box="[1344,1418,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FCA21603DE26BBEB" box="[812,882,1395,1421]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">JODA</collectionCode>
5893, the morphology of the p4 is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D40FFB1BD61FAC41604D8FABBEB" authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1848" box="[1354,1454,1396,1422]" class="Mammalia" family="Odobenidae" genus="Palaeogale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sectoria">
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FAC41604D80DBBEB" box="[1354,1369,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FAE81604D8FABBEB" box="[1382,1454,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">sectoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Lange-Badre &amp; Dashzeveg 1989; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FB1F16E4D825BBC8" author="WANG J. &amp; ZHANG Z. - Q." box="[1169,1393,1427,1454]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="310 - 334" refId="ref8205" refString="WANG J. &amp; ZHANG Z. - Q. 2015. - Phylogenetic analysis on Palaeogale (Palaeogalidae, Carnivora) based on specimens from Oligocene strata of Saint-Jacques, Nei Mongol. Vertebrata PalAsiatica 53 (4): 310 - 334. http: // www. vertpala. ac. cn / EN / Y 2015 / V 53 / I 4 / 310" type="journal article" year="2015">Wang &amp; Zhang 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The size of 
<collectionCode id="ED68AE06FFB1BD61FCFE16C3DEE2BBAB" box="[880,950,1459,1485]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">JODA</collectionCode>
6177 is comparable to 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D40FFB1BD61FB2816C4D85FBBAB" authorityName="Gervais" authorityYear="1848" box="[1190,1291,1459,1485]" class="Mammalia" family="Odobenidae" genus="Palaeogale" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sectoria">
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FB2816C4D9E1BBAB" box="[1190,1205,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FB4D16C4D85FBBAB" box="[1219,1291,1460,1485]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">sectoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F36E7653FFB1BD61FAC416C3D8E4BBAB" box="[1354,1456,1459,1485]" name="Mongolia" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
but the protoconid of the m1 is not expanded (Lange-Badre &amp; Dashzeveg 1989; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FC6C1683D997B86B" author="WANG J. &amp; ZHANG Z. - Q." box="[994,1219,1522,1549]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="310 - 334" refId="ref8205" refString="WANG J. &amp; ZHANG Z. - Q. 2015. - Phylogenetic analysis on Palaeogale (Palaeogalidae, Carnivora) based on specimens from Oligocene strata of Saint-Jacques, Nei Mongol. Vertebrata PalAsiatica 53 (4): 310 - 334. http: // www. vertpala. ac. cn / EN / Y 2015 / V 53 / I 4 / 310" type="journal article" year="2015">Wang &amp; Zhang 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="54C28861FFB1BD61FA881683D867B86B" box="[1286,1331,1523,1549]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">type</typeStatus>
specimen is from the Sharps Formation of South Dakota which is 30-28.6 Ma (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FCEC1542D970B82A" author="MACDONALD J. R." box="[866,1060,1586,1612]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="139 - 240" refId="ref7214" refString="MACDONALD J. R. 1963. - The Miocene Faunas from the Wounded Knee Area of Western South Dakota. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 125 (3): 139 - 240. http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1259" type="journal article" year="1963">MacDonald 1963</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FBBD1542D8CBB82B" author="MCCONNELL T. H. &amp; DIBENEDETTO J. N." box="[1075,1439,1586,1613]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="47759" refId="ref7452" refString="MCCONNELL T. H. &amp; DIBENEDETTO J. N. 2012. - Geology of the Early Arikareean Sharps Formation on the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation and surrounding areas of South Dakota and Nebraska. PloS one 7 (10): e 47759. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0047759" type="journal article" year="2012">McConnell &amp; DiBenedetto 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FCA31522DE9FB80B" author="SWISHER C. C. &amp; III" box="[813,971,1618,1645]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" refId="ref7834" refString="SWISHER C. C. III 1982. - Stratigraphy and Biostratigraphy of the Eastern Portion of the Wildcat Ridge, Western Nebraska. University of Nebraska-Lincoln, 344 p." type="book" year="1982">Swisher (1982)</bibRefCitation>
states that this species is also known from the Brown Siltstone Beds or Whitney Member of the Brule Formation (
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FCBB15E3DE12B8CA" box="[821,838,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">c.</emphasis>
31-30 Ma) and the Unit B Member of the Gering Formation (28.26-28.11 Ma) both of Nebraska (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE84B32FFB1BD61FB6D15C2D8FCB8AA" author="TEDFORD R. H. &amp; SWINEHART J. B. &amp; SWISHER III C. C. &amp; PROTHERO D. R. &amp; KING S. A. &amp; TIERNEY T. E." box="[1251,1448,1714,1740]" pageId="7" pageNumber="432" pagination="312 - 334" refId="ref8070" refString="TEDFORD R. H., SWINEHART J. B., SWISHER III C. C., PROTHERO D. R., KING S. A. &amp; TIERNEY T. E. 1996. - The Whitneyan- Arikareean transition in the High Plains, in PROTHERO D. R. &amp; EMERY R. J. (eds), The Terrestrial Eocene-Oligocene Transition in North America. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge: 312 - 334. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / CBO 9780511665431.016" type="book chapter" year="1996">
Tedford 
<emphasis id="B90DEAD1FFB1BD61FAB215C3D839B8AA" box="[1340,1389,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="432">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
, 
